The paper deals with coding theory, specifically the study of projective Reed-Muller codes and their performance. This falls under the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, such as the determination of Hamming weights, which could place it under Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the study of error-correcting codes is often related to Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of code performance, which could also fall under Signal Processing (cs.SI).
